About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. The show predominantly revolves around 'Jethalaal' (Dilip Joshi), an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbour. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Raj Anankat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or be prepared to leave the premises.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. The show predominantly revolves around 'Jethalaal' (Dilip Joshi), an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbour. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Raj Anankat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or be prepared to leave the premises.

Baap Numbri Beta Dus Numbri is a 1990 Indian Hindi-language action comedy film starring Kader Khan, Shakti Kapoor in pivotal roles. Other cast includes Asrani, Jackie Shroff, Farah, Aditya Pancholi and Anjana Mumtaz. Movie is directed by Aziz Sejawal and produced by Iqbal Baig. It was the 8th highest grossing Indian film of 1990.

Story:

A father and son are conning the whole city of Bombay. Raman, a conman, raises his son, Prasad, to be like him. He swindles his widowed sister for her property, institutionalizes her and abandons her son on a train. 

Raman (Kader Khan) an incorrigible cheat grooms his son Prasad (Shakti Kapoor) in his trade. Master conmen they swindle everybody including Ramans widowed sister Gayatri (Anjana Mumtaz). She is sent to a mental asylum and her son Ravi is abandoned. Ravi grows up to become a local bully Ravi Dada (Jackie Shroff), who extorts money to support his foster sister Anitas (Sabeeha) studies. Ravis competition in the extortion racket Rozy (Farha), but both soon fall in love. Anitas fiancee Anil (Aditya Pancholi) meets Gayatri and brings her home and swears to bring Raman to book. Raman hires Ravi to finish him off. But when Ravi realizes his blunder he repents. Gayatri reunites with her son. Now the threesome of Ravi, Rozy and Anil gang up against the father and son duo on one hand and on the other, swoop down upon Gullu Maharaj (Gulshan Grover), who had exterminated Ravis father - a honest Customs sleuth Pratap Singh (Vijay Arora), a Rozys father DSouza (Bharat Bhushan), who had been killed while trying to save Pratap Singh. A war of wits thus ensues and culminates into an explosion of tummy-tickling laugh riot, a climax extraordinaire!

title: Eid Vlog 2024 with Our Newborn & My Parents
description:
Eid Vlog 2024 with Our Newborn & My Parents

Celebrating was totally different from how it used to be. This time we have our little Liyaan, my parents are with us, nights are somewhat sleepless, and I am running around like i used to when I had my babies, Rehan and Armaan. But it's a complete blessing to have loved ones around and a newborn at home is a miracle. 
I wasn't able to take any clips of last Eid-ul-Fitr as my health was not so great. i was feeling the heaviness of the baby in my womb and the pelvic pain was so bad that i couldn't stand even for 10 minutes continuously. This time, somehow managed to take glimpses of our Liyaan's first Eid though it's incompletely shot.

Hope you all had a great time.

Take care

Love you

How to make kanda khobryache watan recipe - 02:35
*Dry roast white sesame, coriander seeds, cumin seeds & whole spice on low flame & take them out.
*Dry roast futana dal & remove it on the plate.¬†
*Dry roast grated dry coconut on low flame until it turns brown & take them out.
*First dry roast onion for a few minutes, then add some oil to the pan & roast onion until it turns brown in color.
*Add tomatoes & roast until tomatoes get dry & soft & take them out.
*Next¬† roast ginger & garlic for 2 mins.
*Allow everything to cool down completely.
*First, grind¬† all the roasted dry ingredients like sesame, cumin, & whole spices without adding water. .¬†
*Next, grind the roasted coconut , without adding water.¬†
*Then take all wet ingredients like garlic, ginger, some fresh coriander & make a paste.
*Lastly, grind tomatoes & onions without adding water.¬†
*In a pan, take all the grinded ingredients together, add salt¬† & mix it well with hands.¬†
*After this ,again grind this mixture in the mixer to fine paste without adding water.¬†
*Add around 2 tbsp oil to this while grinding it.¬†
*Our watan is ready, you can store this into an airtight container for 10-12 days in the refrigerator
